claim.claim-text:
12. The apparatus of claim 1, further comprising: 
a selector switch having multiple settings and being movable between said multiple settings; 
said pedal being arranged and configured to operate a plurality of surgical power tools, said plurality of surgical power tools being a number substantially equivalent to number of multiple settings of said selector switch; 
wherein said selector switch alternates application of said pedal between operating one of said plurality of surgical power tools and another of said plurality of surgical power tools.

18. The apparatus of claim 13, further comprising: 
a second selector switch disposed on said second pedal platform, said second selector switch having multiple settings and being movable between said multiple settings; 
said pedal of said second pedal platform being arranged and configured to operate a plurality of surgical power tools, said plurality of surgical power tools being a number substantially equivalent to a number of multiple settings of said selector switch; 
wherein said second selector switch alternates application of said pedal between one of said plurality of surgical power tools and another of said plurality of surgical power tools.

25. The apparatus of claim 19, further comprising: 
a second pedal platform means comprising at least one operational means, said operational means being arranged and configured to be movable between a depressed position and a released position; 
said operational means of said second pedal platform means receiving power from a power supply and being arranged and configured to operate the surgical power tool.

26. A universal surgical power tool pedal apparatus comprising: 
a first pedal platform having a pedal aperture disposed therein, said pedal aperture being arranged and configured to releasably receive and support a pedal therein; 
said pedal being arranged and configured to be movable between a depressed position and a released position, wherein said pedal operates a power surgical tool when said pedal is disposed in the depressed position.

27. The apparatus of claim 26, further comprising: 
a pedal identifier disposed on said first pedal platform such that said pedal identifier is substantially aligned with said pedal aperture; 
wherein said pedal identifier is arranged and configured to indicate to a user the location of said pedal aperture without the user viewing the apparatus.

29. The apparatus of claim 26, further comprising: 
a plurality of pedal apertures disposed in said first pedal platform, each of said plurality of pedal apertures being arranged and configured to releasably receive and support a separate pedal therein; 
each of said pedals being arranged and configured to be movable between a depressed position and a released position individually, wherein each of said pedals operates a separate power surgical tool when said pedal is disposed in the depressed position.

30. The apparatus of claim 29, further comprising: 
a plurality of pedal identifiers disposed on said first pedal platform such that each of said plurality of pedal identifiers is substantially aligned with a different one of said plurality of pedal apertures; 
wherein said plurality of pedal identifiers is arranged and configured to indicate to a user the location of each pedal aperture without looking at the apparatus.

31. The apparatus of claim 26, further comprising: 
a second pedal platform having a pedal aperture disposed therein, said pedal aperture being arranged and configured to releasably receive and support a pedal therein; 
said pedal being arranged and configured to be movable between a depressed position and a released position, wherein said pedal operates a power surgical tool when said pedal is disposed in the depressed position.

32. The apparatus of claim 31, further comprising: 
a pedal identifier disposed on said second pedal platform such that said pedal identifier is substantially aligned with said pedal aperture; 
wherein said pedal identifier is arranged and configured to indicate to a user the location of said pedal aperture without looking at the apparatus.

33. The apparatus of claim 31, further comprising: 
a plurality of pedal apertures disposed in said second pedal platform, each of said plurality of pedal apertures being arranged and configured to releasably receive and support a separate pedal therein; 
wherein each of said pedals is arranged and configured to operate a different surgical power tool and the same power tool as a pedal disposed in a corresponding pedal aperture disposed in said first pedal platform.

34. The apparatus of claim 33, further comprising: 
a plurality of pedal identifiers such that each of said plurality of pedal identifiers is substantially aligned with a different one of said plurality of pedal apertures; 
wherein each of said plurality of pedal identifiers is arranged and configured to indicate to a user the location of one of said pedal apertures without looking at the apparatus.

35. A control apparatus for an operating room, comprising: 
a first pedal platform comprising at least one pedal being adapted to move between a depressed position and released position; 
wherein said pedal is adapted to be operated by a human foot and said pedal is adapted to operate a powered element in the operating room.
